AB  - The Adult Attachment Interview (AAI; George, Kaplan, & Main, 1996) is a rich clinical and research instrument. In a matter of 60-90 minutes, it is possible with this instrument to uncover characteristic ways that the individual approaches attachment-relevant memories, thoughts, and feelings. The AAI reveals the individual's 'state of mind with regard to attachment' (Main, Goldwyn, & Hesse, 2003). In our work, we have developed an intervention program to help foster parents provide nurturing, sensitive care to their children. The task for parent trainers is very different depending on parents' state of mind. The AAI is integral to what we do in terms of tailoring a manualized treatment procedure, and in the predictions we make regarding treatment use and effectiveness. In this chapter, we describe the use of the AAI in this work. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2018 APA, all rights reserved)
